From: Jacob Keller <jacob.e.keller@intel.com>
Date: Mon, 8 Jul 2019 16:12:25 -0700
Subject: fm10k: reduce the scope of the local i variable
Patch-mainline: v5.4-rc1
Git-commit: d56b47791d3464178be2aa2d61db694331d50d5a
References: jsc#SLE-8009

Reduce the scope of the local loop variable in the
fm10k_check_hang_subtask function.

This was detected by cppcheck and resolves the following warning
produced by that tool:

[driver/fm10k_pci.c:852]: (style) The scope of the variable 'i' can be
reduced.

Signed-off-by: Jacob Keller <jacob.e.keller@intel.com>
Tested-by: Andrew Bowers <andrewx.bowers@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jeff Kirsher <jeffrey.t.kirsher@intel.com>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/fm10k/fm10k_pci.c |    4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/fm10k/fm10k_pci.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/fm10k/fm10k_pci.c
@@ -698,8 +698,6 @@ static void fm10k_watchdog_subtask(struc
  */
 static void fm10k_check_hang_subtask(struct fm10k_intfc *interface)
 {
-	int i;
-
 	/* If we're down or resetting, just bail */
 	if (test_bit(__FM10K_DOWN, interface->state) ||
 	    test_bit(__FM10K_RESETTING, interface->state))
@@ -711,6 +709,8 @@ static void fm10k_check_hang_subtask(str
 	interface->next_tx_hang_check = jiffies + (2 * HZ);
 
 	if (netif_carrier_ok(interface->netdev)) {
+		int i;
+
 		/* Force detection of hung controller */
 		for (i = 0; i < interface->num_tx_queues; i++)
 			set_check_for_tx_hang(interface->tx_ring[i]);
